t, chicken is next, beef and fries hold.',\n      sales: 'Mozzarella is the input that gates pizza this weekend. Topping it up is what lets the floor sell the promotion.',\n      procurement: 'The costed order is priced at live vendor rates and timed to lead times. One tap drafts it for confirmation.',\n      qa: 'Days of cover with fresh counts flags slow movers before they age out, protecting freshness and food safety.' },\n    demand: {\n      finance: 'Building beef and fries to a rising forecast protects sales capture, while easing chicken avoids cash tied in stock that would spoil.',\n      ops: 'The forecast already blends last year, recent weeks and the promotion. Set par to it rather than copying last week.',\n      sales: 'Beef and fries are trending up, so make sure the floor never runs short on the lines guests want most.',\n      procurement: 'Lift beef and fries orders to match the rise and trim chicken. Stage the build ahead of supplier lead times.',\n      qa: 'Right sizing to demand keeps stock turning, so ingredients stay within shelf life and spec.' },\n    labor: {\n      finance: 'Right sizing the week protects about $1,900 of sales and removes Saturday overtime. A point of labour at a $20k outlet is over $10k a year.',\n      ops: 'Hours are close to right but on the wrong days. Move cover from Sunday to the Friday and Saturday peaks.',\n      sales: 'Your busiest 90 minutes is understaffed. Cover the Friday peak so service stays fast and attach stays high.',\n      procurement: 'Staffing runs off the same demand forecast that sizes your orders, so plan labour and stock together for the week.',\n      qa: 'Adequate cover on peak protects food safety and standards, since rushed shifts are where checks slip.' },\n    season: {\n      finance: 'Summer input costs squeeze GP per ticket. Shifting the menu mix to grills protects margin without a price rise.',\n      ops: 'Plan the menu and prep around the inputs that are climbing. Grills and lighter 