itted.', money: '8 to 1 return' } },\n      coo: { headline: 'The forecast already sized this. The only open step is your confirmation.',\n        sections: [\n          { h: 'The process read', p: 'Demand forecast, recipe, count and vendor price are already joined into one suggested order. The system has done the work. What remains is a human confirmation before anything is placed.' },\n          { h: 'Why it scales', p: 'The same logic runs for every line and every outlet, so a manager confirms rather than calculates. That is what keeps ordering consistent across the estate.' },\n        ],\n        rec: { text: 'Confirm to send. Apply the same suggested order flow to the other promotion lines.', money: 'one tap' } },\n      sales: { headline: 'Do not let a stockout cap your biggest sales weekend.',\n        sections: [\n          { h: 'The opportunity', p: 'The promotion is forecast to lift covers 18%. Mozzarella is the one input that gates pizza sales, so the order is what lets the floor actually capture the weekend.' },\n          { h: 'What to line up', p: 'With stock secured, brief the team to push pizza and the side of chips together for the highest margin ticket.' },\n        ],\n        rec: { text: 'Secure stock, then brief the floor to push pizza and sides through the promotion.', money: 'protects $3,100 GP' } },\n    },\n    waste: {\n      outlet: { headline: 'Waste is $120 this week, up 18% and the highest in six weeks. Herbs and salad lead it.',\n        sections: [\n          { h: 'What is happening', p: 'Produce waste is $120 against a $90 target and has climbed for three weeks. Most of it is over prep on quieter weekdays rather than spoilage, so it is controllable through the next order.' },\n          { h: 'The loop back', p: 'Waste feeds straight into the next produce order. Trimming the order and tightening prep on Tuesday and Wednesday pulls it back toward target.' },\n        ],\n        rec: { text: 'Cut the next produce order about 10% and 